cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.NE, cs.AI, cs.CL 

The paper discusses techniques for accelerating the training of neural networks, which is a common topic in the machine learning community. The focus is on transferring knowledge from one network to another, which is a technique commonly used in deep learning. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also specifically mentions improving accuracy on the ImageNet dataset, which is a common computer vision benchmark, suggesting cs.CV (Computer Vision) as another likely category. The techniques discussed involve modifying the structure of neural networks, which could fall under cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) or cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Finally, the paper discusses the use of natural language processing techniques, which could suggest cs.CL (Computation and Language) as a possible category.
